## ðŸ” Security Best Practices

### Environment Variables

**DO:**
- âœ… Store in `.env` for local development
- âœ… Use Secret Manager for sensitive values in production
- âœ… Never commit `.env` to git
- âœ… Use different values for dev/staging/prod

**DON'T:**
- âŒ Hardcode secrets in code
- âŒ Log sensitive values
- âŒ Share secrets via insecure channels
- âŒ Use same secrets across environments

### Service Accounts

**DO:**
- âœ… Use principle of least privilege
- âœ… Grant only required roles
- âœ… Audit permissions regularly
- âœ… Use separate service accounts per service

**DON'T:**
- âŒ Use Owner role for service accounts
- âŒ Share service account keys
- âŒ Grant overly broad permissions
- âŒ Skip permission reviews

### Firestore Security Rules

```javascript
// Deploy security rules
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    // Users can only access their own data
    match /conversations/{conversationId} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null && 
        resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid;
    }
    
    match /messages/{messageId} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null && 
        resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid;
    }
  }
}
```

**Deploy:**
```bash
firebase deploy --only firestore:rules --project gen-lang-client-0986191192
```

